<title>USA: Informix rescinds stock repurchase offer.</title>
<headline>Informix rescinds stock repurchase offer.</headline>
<dateline>MENLO PARK, Calif. 1996-09-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Informix Corp said on Monday it was rescinding a stock repurchase program.</p>
<p>Informix said its board voted to rescind the program to comply with a Securities and Exchange Commission issuance affecting acquisitions that involve a pooling of interests or stock-for-stock transactions.</p>
<p>In the past year Informix has bought Stanford Technology Group and Illustra Information Technologies through poolings of interest.  </p>
<p>Informix said it had about 4.4 million shares authorized for repurchase before the buyback was cancelled.</p>
<p>Informix Corp's subsidiary, Informix Software Inc, provides database technology for businesses.</p>
